You are deploying an LLM server where model loading takes 30+ seconds. Which approach best avoids reloading the model on every request?

A.
```python
@app.function(gpu="H100")
def generate(prompt):
    engine = load_model()
    return engine.generate(prompt)
```

B.
```python
@app.function(gpu="H100")
def generate(prompt):
    return cached_engine.generate(prompt)
```

C.
```python
@app.cls(gpu="H100")
class VLLMServer:
    _engine = None

    @modal.enter()
    def startup(self):
        self._engine = load_model()

    @modal.method()
    def generate(self, prompt):
        return self._engine.generate(prompt)
```

D.
